# AI FAQ Site Rules

## General Guidelines
- Site is written in Traditional Chinese (繁體中文)
- Use Astro framework with Tailwind CSS
- Site is deployed to GitHub Pages at `/ai-resources-for-teachers/` base path

## FAQ Management

### Adding New FAQs
**CRITICAL: ALWAYS append new FAQs to the END of the array. NEVER rearrange the order.**

Reason: Each FAQ has an anchor link based on its position (e.g., `#faq-1`, `#faq-2`). Rearranging questions will break existing shared links.

### FAQ Structure
```javascript
{
  question: "問題文字",
  answer: "回答文字",
  source: "https://source-url.com" // Optional: include if citing external source
}
```

### FAQ File Locations
- Gemini FAQs: `src/pages/faq/gemini.astro`
- NotebookLM FAQs: `src/pages/faq/notebooklm.astro`
- Google Workspace FAQs: `src/pages/faq/google-workspace.astro`

### When Adding Source Citations
- Include `source` field with full URL
- Template will automatically display "查看來源" link
- Mention source in answer text (e.g., "資料來源：Google Workspace for Education 官方文檔")

## Resource Showcase

### Adding New Resources
Resources are listed in `src/pages/index.astro`

Structure:
```javascript
{
  title: "資源標題",
  author: "作者名稱",
  description: "詳細描述，可包含使用的工具和技術",
  link: "https://demo-url.com", // GitHub Pages or live demo
  github: "https://github.com/user/repo", // Optional
  tags: ["Tag1", "Tag2", "Tag3"] // Max 3-4 tags
}
```

### Resource Guidelines
- Get author approval before adding their projects
- Include both demo link and GitHub link when available
- Mention if created using AI tools (Gemini, Cursor, etc.)
- Use descriptive tags that help categorize the resource

## Styling Conventions
- Primary color: Indigo (`indigo-600`)
- Success/Answer color: Green (`green-600`)
- Question numbers: Indigo bold
- Cards: White background with subtle shadow and border
- Hover effects: Use Tailwind's `group` and `group-hover` patterns

## Footer Content
- Content source: HKACE AI for Education WhatsApp 社群
- Site builder: 10 教育
- Include GitHub repository link

## Commit Messages
- Use clear, descriptive commit messages in English
- Format: "Action: description of changes"
- Examples:
  - "Add new FAQ about X feature"
  - "Update footer content"
  - "Fix anchor scroll offset"

## GitHub Pages Deployment
- Base path is `/ai-resources-for-teachers/`
- Use `import.meta.env.BASE_URL` for internal links
- `.nojekyll` file required in `public/` directory
- GitHub Actions automatically deploys on push to main

